<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-05-16T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-05-16T18:00:00-05:00" n="676" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d676">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">611.4731/103: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Consul General at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-05-16T19:00:00-04:00">May
                                        16, 1934—7 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Fundamental issue is diversion of traffic of American origin from
                                American to Canadian railroads and ports, halted in 1929 but resumed
                                when agreement became effective. We gave you language identic with
                                Canadian for purpose of securing privilege identic with that now
                                enjoyed by Canada.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>